                                                Giant Manufacturing Company Limited
                                             Company Snapshot
                                            









                                            
	Giant Manufacturing Company Limited operates within the Motorcycles, bicycles, and parts sector.
	
	In addition to historical fundamental analyses, the complete report available to purchase compares Giant Manufacturing Company Limited with three other
	motorcycle manufacturers in Asia:
		
	Loncin Motor Co Ltd
	
		of China
		(2016
	sales of 8.48 billion Chinese Renmimbi [US$1.26  billion]
		of which 40%
		was Two-wheeled Motor Vehicle),
	
	Sanyang Industry Company Limited
	
		(35.45 billion Taiwanese Dollars [US$1.17  billion]
		of which 79%
		was Taiwan Department), and
	
	Yadea Group Holdings Ltd
	
		which is
		
		based in Hong Kong
		(7.77 billion Hong Kong Dollars [US$995.10  million]
		).
	
	Sales Analysis. 
	
		During the year ended December of 2016, sales at
		Giant Manufacturing Company Limited were 57.09 billion Taiwanese Dollars (US$1.89 billion).
	
		This
		
			is
		
			a
			
			decrease of 5.5%
		
		 versus 2015, when the company's sales were 60.42 billion Taiwanese Dollars.
	
		Contributing to the drop in overall sales was the 34.2% decline
		in Materials, from 5.78 billion Taiwanese Dollars to 3.80 billion Taiwanese Dollars.
		
					There were also decreases in sales in
					Bicycles (down 4.4% to 51.95 billion Taiwanese Dollars)
				.
		
					However, these declines were partially offset by the increase in sales of
					Other Segment (up 347.2% to 1.34 billion Taiwanese Dollars)
				
			.
		

	





 


 
 


 
 


 
 











 



 













 










